						               													<description>Detective Ray vs P the thief is a mirco game for 150 bg convention. The concept is from my 5 years old son. Keep the core the game and extend the game play by creating 2 more expansions for the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Base game:&amp;#10;Start player flips the card. If the flipped cards are 3 in row, the the active player win the game. If not, the opponent close the eyes and the active player must reorganise the flipped cards and flip them over. The game continues unitl the end confidtion is meet.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Tool Expansion:&amp;#10;During the setup, the players randomly choose a tool card. They can use the power of the tool card the whole game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3/4 players Expansion:&amp;#10;Add 7 cards to the base game. The players may guess who is the thief during the turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Mission Expansion:&amp;#10;During the setup, the players randomly choose 2 mission cards. If they flip the cards set as same as the mission card, the players finish the mission card and gain one victory point. The player who is the first player gain 2 victory points wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
